The presidential primary of All Progressive Congress (APC) is currently taking place at Abuja, the primary commenced yesterday night and it’s expected to be concluded today. During the presidential primary yesterday night, a song by Timi Dakolo that is titled “Great Nation” was played, the Nigerian singer and song writer has taken to twitter to express how he feels about his song being played at APC’s presidential primary.
Few hours ago, Timi Dakolo posted a tweet in which he enquired why the song of an artiste will be played in a rally or campaign without the permission of the artiste, he also stated that this is second time it has happened.

The Nigerians on twitter that reacted to the tweet Timi Dakolo posted had different opinions, some of them were in support of what he said while others were not in support.



